Dec 8 2008 	Great Budget Hotel	Yes the area isn't Union Square but this is probably one of the best budget hotels in San Francisco. The entire hotel was recently gutted and completely remodeled. I usually stay at other properties on 7th St but they were all sold out for a citywide convention that was in town so I decided to try this hotel out.I got a $99 rate and I think the hotel was worth that price. I was in the main hotel building, not the motel-style set-up next to the main building. The rooms are very small. You basically have the space around the bed to walk around and there isn't a desk (just a small round table - see pics, the table is in front of the green chair). Free WiFi is always good. The bed was comfortable and the small flat screen TV on the wall was fine too. It's difficult to find anything wrong with the room itself since everything is brand new. I would recommend this hotel for 1-2 people max in the same room. Any family with kids will need more space. I think it's ideal for the young traveler on a budget.The only things I didn't like are as follows:- No temperature controls. I was there in early December and luckily it was cool at night so I could open the windows as the room was always on the warm side and I like a cool room. Think of your room here as that apartment you lived in where the only way to regulate the temperature was to open or close the windows. If I had been here in the summer or if the nights weren't cool, I would have been uncomfortable. There is a fan in the room but when it was on the chains rattled and the fan was loud. I tried sleeping with it on one night and I would keep waking up because of the noise. - Light: The shutters on the windows look great, but they don't block any light at all. The sun would be streaming into my room and by 8am I just gave up trying to get back to sleep.- Windows open = Cool, but noisy. I live in Chicago off lake shore drive so I am used to the sounds of traffic with the windows open. However, the traffic on that street is LOUD. Trucks backing up and beeping, people yelling, the parking for the hotel was right outside my window. Between the sunlight streaming in and the noise with the window open...I needed to take a nap each day (after sunset) so I would be ready to go out and meet friends in the evening.	
Nov 18 2008 	Loved it!! Central Location!!	The hotel is new, chic, and very stylish! We stayed in a Courtyard Queen room, and it was fabulous and VERY clean! Definately would stay here again when I return to SF. Contrary to other reviewers, my wife and I did not find the neighborhood that &quot;bad&quot; or &quot;sketchy.&quot; SOMA is reinventing itself and just like any big city the area has its share of bums and needy people. We stayed there for 5 days and frequently returned late at night and had to walk 2 short blocks from the F-line and BART to the hotel. Never once were we approached by anyone. When visiting any big city, just maintain your awareness and don't be so afraid of the unfamiliar. The Good Hotel is a gem of a find in a plethora of other name-brand subpar hotels.	
